Appendix A: Proof of Strong Convexity of \mathcal{J}(L) (Sketch)

Under the assumption that the Euler-Lagrange operator is linear in L (which holds for Lagrangians of the form L = T - V with kinetic energy quadratic in velocities), the mismatch term \int |\dot{J}_{\text{obs}}|^2 dt is quadratic in L. The regularization term \lambda\|L-L_0\|^2 is also quadratic and strongly convex. Hence \mathcal{J} is strongly convex with modulus \mu = 2\lambda (plus contributions from the mismatch's Hessian). For general nonlinear Lagrangians, local strong convexity holds in a neighborhood of L_0 under mild non-degeneracy conditions.

