Appendix B: Derivation of the Curvature Correction in Itô's Lemma

Let M be a Riemannian manifold with Levi-Civita connection \nabla. For an SDE in Stratonovich form dp_t = b(p_t) dt + \sigma(p_t) \circ dW_t, the Itô form includes a correction term involving the Christoffel symbols. For a function V, the Itô formula reads

dV = \left( \nabla V(b) + \frac12 \operatorname{Tr}\left( \sigma^\mathsf{T} \operatorname{Hess} V \,\sigma \right) + \frac12 \operatorname{Ric}(\sigma,\sigma) \right) dt + (\nabla V)^\mathsf{T}\sigma \, dW_t,
\]  

where \operatorname{Ric}(\sigma,\sigma) = \sum_{i,j,k,l} \sigma^{ik} \sigma^{jl} R_{ijkl} and R is the Riemann curvature tensor. See Elworthy (1982) for details.

